Subject: [PATCH 13/13] Fix GenerateTelosSummary.ts parser bugs

Upstream issue: danielmiessler/Personal_AI_Infrastructure#1140

Three independent parser bugs in
PAI/TOOLS/GenerateTelosSummary.ts cause the auto-generated
PRINCIPAL_TELOS.md (loaded into the DA's context at every session
start via CLAUDE.md @-import) to silently miss most of the user's
TELOS data.

Bug 1 — parseItems() only matches bullet form
  parseItems matches /^-\s+\*?\*?(\w+)\*?\*?:\s*(.+)/  i.e. only
  "- **M0**: text". But canonical PAI source files (after
  /interview, /migrate, or hand-edits) use header form:
    ### M0: Family Presence
  parseItems returns 0 items, so all 5 callers (parseMissions,
  parseGoals, parseNarratives, parseChallenges, parseModels)
  yield empty arrays.
  Fix: extend parseItems to also try header form
  /^#{2,4}\s+([A-Z]+\d+):\s*(.+?)(?:\s*\(.*\))?\s*$/. Bullet wins
  if present (preserves prior behaviour); header is the fallback.
  Trailing "(parenthetical)" is stripped (e.g. "### M0: Health
  (FY2026)" → text "Health").

Bug 2 — hardcoded {{PRINCIPAL_FULL_NAME}} placeholder
  Line 220 hardcodes "# Principal TELOS — {{PRINCIPAL_FULL_NAME}}"
  with no substitution mechanism in this generator. The literal
  {{...}} token reaches the file and the DA boots seeing it.
  Fix: add getPrincipalName() that reads settings.json
  principal.fullName || principal.name (matching the schema written
  by the installer in config-gen.ts:56-59), falling back to "User"
  if settings.json is missing/malformed. Use template literal at
  the call site.

Bug 3 — parseTraumas() requires ID-prefixed items
  parseTraumas calls parseItems (which expects TR0/TR1/... IDs),
  but the canonical/bootstrap TRAUMAS.md uses plain titled headers:
    ### Religious Worldview Shift
    ### Divorce
  parseItems returns 0, the section in the generated summary is
  empty.
  Fix: try parseItems first; if 0 items, fall back to extracting
  /^###\s+(.+)$/gm header titles and assigning synthetic TR0..TRn.
  Empty TRAUMAS.md still returns [].

Files touched (paths relative to upstream source root):

  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/TOOLS/GenerateTelosSummary.ts          :42, 49, 188, 217

Total: 1 file, 4 hunks.

Co-existence: no prior patch (0001-0012) modifies this file.

Hunks generated via diff -u against extracted upstream tarball.
No hand-counted @@ headers.

Impact: PRINCIPAL_TELOS.md is @-imported into the DA's system
context every session. Before this fix, the DA boots blind to
missions, goals, narratives, challenges, formative experiences,
and the principal name. After, all four parsers handle both
bullet and header forms; principal name reflects settings.json;
TRAUMAS.md works with or without ID prefixes.
---
--- a/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/TOOLS/GenerateTelosSummary.ts
+++ b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/TOOLS/GenerateTelosSummary.ts
@@ -42,6 +42,22 @@
 }
 
 /**
+ * Resolve the principal's display name from settings.json, falling back
+ * to a generic label. Replaces the literal {{PRINCIPAL_FULL_NAME}} token
+ * that previously shipped in the generated summary header.
+ */
+function getPrincipalName(): string {
+  try {
+    const path = join(process.env.HOME || '', '.claude/settings.json');
+    if (!existsSync(path)) return 'User';
+    const settings = JSON.parse(readFileSync(path, 'utf-8'));
+    return settings.principal?.fullName || settings.principal?.name || 'User';
+  } catch {
+    return 'User';
+  }
+}
